<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">

    <!-- Always force latest IE rendering engine or request Chrome Frame -->
    <meta content="IE=edge,chrome=1" http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible">

    <!-- Use title if it's in the page YAML frontmatter -->
    <title><%= current_page.data.title || "Installfest by ReInteractive" %></title>

    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "guides" %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag  "all" %>
  </head>

  <body class="<%= page_classes %>">
    <%= partial 'header' %>
    <article class="main">
      <aside>
        <h3>Guides</h3>
        <h4>Installfest Rails 4.2</h4>
        <p>This guide is based on Rails 4.2</p>
        <ul>
          <li><%= link_to 'Getting Started',          '/guides/installfest42/getting_started' %></li>
          <li><%= link_to 'Finishing a Basic Blog',   '/guides/installfest42/finishing_a_basic_blog' %></li>
          <li><%= link_to 'Testing the Blog',         '/guides/installfest42/testing_the_blog' %></li>
          <li><%= link_to 'Admin and Markdown',       '/guides/installfest42/admin_and_markdown' %></li>
          <li><%= link_to 'Understanding Migrations', '/guides/installfest42/understanding_migrations' %></li>
          <li><%= link_to 'Assets and Errors',        '/guides/installfest42/assets_and_errors' %></li></br>
        </ul>

        <h3>Further Help</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><%= link_to 'Getting Started on Mavericks or Yosemite', '/guides/installfest41/rails_on_mavericks' %></li>
           <p>This guide will help you get Rails installed if you are on Mavericks or Yosemite.</p>
          <li><%= link_to 'Command and Phrase Cheat Sheet', '/guides/installfest/cheat_sheet' %></li>
           <p>This cheat sheet helps you understand a bit more about what your Installfest code is actually doing.</p>
          <li><%= link_to 'A bit about Web development',    '/guides/installfest/web_development' %></li>
            <p>If you are new to web development, this guide helps explain the difference between front end and back end web development.</p>
          <li><%= link_to 'A bit about Ruby and Rails',     '/guides/installfest/ruby_rails' %></li>
           <p>This guide explains a little more about Ruby and Rails.</p>
          <li><%= link_to 'Further Online Help',            '/guides/installfest/further_help' %></li>
            <p>These are a few links to help you continue your Ruby and Rails learning. </p>
        </ul>

        </aside>
      <article class="guide">
        <%= yield %>
        <%= partial 'comments' %>
      </article>
    </article>

    <%= partial 'footer' %>
    <%= partial 'tracking' %>
  </body>
</html>
